<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99151035326893></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99151035326893><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=99151035326893>money</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jun 2nd 3:32 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Im a level 9 bard, and fairly new to everquest.  I was wonder what is the best way for someone my level to make money.  I've tried selling HQ cat pelts, but they don't sell for that much, and hardly anybody ever wants them.<br>I'm so broke i don't even own a magical weapon and i was using a bronze weapon until a very kind halfling gave me some charity.<br><br>Also, what are the best armour/weapons for someone my level?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99254559128046></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99254559128046><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=99254559128046>RE: money</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jun 14th 3:06 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are a 9th level Bard and have a magic weapon, you should absolutely be on Erud's Crossing Island (wisp island).  I am there with my bard and have been since 9th or so.  It is great XP hunting wisps, although tough solo at 9th.  The key is collecting the Lightstones and Greater Lightstones.  When you fill up all you can hold of these, speedsong your way to North Karana gypsy camp.  Be careful as there are griffawns and lions about.  Hand all your stones to the gypsy lady named Mersila (sp?) and she will in return give you several types of books.  This is a wizard research quest for good races, and for the GLS she will return a Concordance of Research which if you turn around and sell to another gypsy yields about 9pp.  Great xp for the quest on each stone and lots of pp.  Be aware though, that the Concordance is a container, so leave at least one slot open on your run to NK.<br><br>-Aliver of Bristlebane<br> Bard of the 13th song<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
